# SystemAnalyzer — Project Architecture & Data Flow

## What This Project Is

SystemAnalyzer is a COBOL dependency analysis platform. It discovers, maps, and visualizes how legacy COBOL programs, DB2 tables, files, and copybooks relate to each other in the Dedge ecosystem. The pipeline starts from a small set of "seed" programs (menu screens, batch jobs) and iteratively expands outward through CALL chains, SQL references, and RAG-assisted discovery until the full dependency graph is mapped.

The output is a set of JSON files consumed by a web UI that renders interactive dependency graphs (GoJS + Mermaid), with filtering, drill-down context menus, export/import, and a detail panel for every node.

